    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-05-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Harris</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-05-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 17.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 6, of the 9th instant, relative to the liability of Mr. H. M. Braem
                    to income tax under the laws of Austria.</p>
                <p>In reply I have to inform you that the matter is one which should be tested in
                    the courts of that country. In its present aspect, at least, the case is not one
                    for diplomatic intervention.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
